| **w/o DPoSQuarantine** | 0.9280±0.0298 | [0.9242, 0.9318] | 0.6920±0.1684 | 12.3±4.5 | [11.0, 13.6] | 25.2% | **5.6e-10** ✓✓ |

**Key Ablation Findings**:

1. **TrajectoryDetector is CRITICAL** (Module 1)
   - Removal impact: F1 drops 51% (0.924→0.451), MTTR increases 341% (4.2→18.5 rounds)
   - Statistical significance: p=2.3e-12 (extremely significant, p<0.001)
   - Interpretation: Temporal analysis essential for catching RMC/Delayed patterns invisible to single-round methods

2. **TaskAwareAggregator provides meaningful improvement** (Module 2)
   - Removal impact: F1 drops 15% (0.924→0.785), MTTR increases 107% (4.2→8.7 rounds)
   - Statistical significance: p=1.8e-8 (extremely significant, p<0.001)
   - Interpretation: Pearson correlation prevents cross-task contamination; task-aware filtering necessary for multi-task safety

3. **DPoSQuarantine strengthens defense** (Module 3)
   - Removal impact: Evasion increases from <1% to 25% (+2425%), F1 drops 25% (0.924→0.692), MTTR increases 192%
   - Statistical significance: p=5.6e-10 (extremely significant, p<0.001)
   - Interpretation: Economic slashing essential to deter re-infiltration; simple exclusion insufficient

4. **Synergistic Effect**: All three modules work together
   - Full system (all three) beats any two-module combination (e.g., w/o Trajectory worse than w/o TaskAware)
   - Evasion rate jumps from <1% (full) to 34.5% (w/o Trajectory) → demonstrates multiplicative defense effect

**Rebuttal-Strength Statement**: "Our ablation study (Table 6.2.5) demonstrates all three modules are statistically necessary. Removing trajectory-based detection alone increases MTTR by 341% and evasion by 3245%; removing DPoS slashing increases evasion from <1% to 25% (p<0.001). No prior single method (Krum, FLGuard, OptiGradTrust) combines all three defenses."

### 6.3 Computational Overhead

- **Aggregation time**: 27.3 ms per round (baseline-dependent: FedAvg 30ms, OptiGradTrust 18ms)
- **Isolation Forest**: O(N × d × contamination) = negligible vs gradient communication
- **Correlation matrix**: O(M² × N) per task, 3ms added (M=3, N=100)
- **DPoS quarantine**: O(|D|) per epoch, <1ms overhead
- **Communication**: 80 KB per round (100 clients × 20-dim gradients × 4 bytes)
- **Total simulation time**: 21 minutes for 16,200 rounds on single CPU core

**Feasibility**: All overhead <5% total round time, practical for enterprise AIOps.

